00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:24.000
You're on next Wednesday?

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:26.000
Yes.

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:33.000
So how have you both found the last seven months?

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:38.000
The first couple of months we didn't ever see each other, did we Richard?

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:40.000
No we didn't.

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:50.000
We were able to keep in contact through Skype and video calling and things and phone of course.

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:55.000
So why didn't you, was it just the lockdown?

00:01:55.000 --> 00:02:04.000
It was, we were locked down, I think we were confused what we could see and don't think we were allowed to see outside.

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:05.000
Yes.

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:07.000
A little tickler time.

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:12.000
But then when it got a bit easier we were going out for walks.

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:13.000
Yes.

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:16.000
Every day.

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
A source of this to meet us.

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:21.000
Yep.

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:30.000
Then when we were there we were able to go and stay in your house when we went.

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:32.000
Yes, when the bubble started.

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:34.000
So you bubbled with each other did you?

00:02:34.000 --> 00:02:35.000
Yes.

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:43.000
And how did you find that after a few months away from each other, what was it like seeing each other in person for the first time?

00:02:43.000 --> 00:02:44.000
Relief.

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:46.000
Yes, it was pure joy.

00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:49.000
Joy.

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:55.000
And what did you miss about being apart when you couldn't see each other?

00:02:55.000 --> 00:02:58.000
What?

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:00.000
It was the company really wasn't it?

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:02.000
Yes, I think company mostly.

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:04.000
Yes.

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:09.000
Attempting not to kill each other but if you know what I mean Paul.

00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:14.000
I know what you mean, I'm married.

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:20.000
Watching the same programmes, laughing at things, I think we mostly missed as well.

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:22.000
Yes.

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:24.000
So.

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:26.000
And talking to each other.

00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:28.000
Yep.

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:35.000
Forgive me if you don't want to answer this but when you stayed at each others homes did you stay in the same bedroom, in the same bed?

00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:38.000
Yes, didn't we Ed?

00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:39.000
Yes.

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:43.000
Was there any aspect of that that you missed in the months that you weren't together?

00:03:43.000 --> 00:03:46.000
No.

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:52.000
When I say no it's the snoring part of it Paul.

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:54.000
You're a snorer Richard.

00:03:54.000 --> 00:03:57.000
Yes, unfortunately.

00:03:57.000 --> 00:04:03.000
Rather than that I did miss it about the snoring.

00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:09.000
We did miss each other apart from the snoring part.

00:04:09.000 --> 00:04:18.000
And you say companionship, is it different do you think than just talking to each other over the internet?

00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:21.000
Yes, definitely.

00:04:21.000 --> 00:04:25.000
Can you tell me in what way it's different for you?

00:04:26.000 --> 00:04:40.000
It's like when you can see someone on screen you can't always, how can I put this, it's the physicality of not having somebody near to you or next to you.

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:46.000
I agree with that.

00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:48.000
Yeah.

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:52.000
Where do you both live at the moment?

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:55.000
At the moment we're apart.

00:04:55.000 --> 00:04:57.000
I live on my own.

00:04:57.000 --> 00:05:00.000
And I live with my parents.

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:05.000
Richard, do you live on your own completely or do you have any support coming in?

00:05:05.000 --> 00:05:13.000
I do have support but not from my parents. My father missed them, I live across the road from me to the few doors up.

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:17.000
So they're there if I ever need them and they've been absolutely fantastic.

00:05:17.000 --> 00:05:25.000
So when the first lockdown happened in March Richard, did you stay on your own?

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:31.000
I did, yeah, we were talking on the doorsteps and short distances.

00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:39.000
And how did you find that apart from obviously missing Helen, how did you find just being on your own for that amount of time?

00:05:39.000 --> 00:05:43.000
Up and down.

00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:49.000
Sometimes I felt OK most of the time because I knew they were only a phone call away order, I could talk on the doorstep to them.

00:05:49.000 --> 00:05:55.000
But when things got easier then we were able to meet outside, I was able to go and see them in the garden.

00:05:55.000 --> 00:05:59.000
And that was OK and that was good.

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:04.000
Was there anything you enjoyed about not being able to go anywhere or do anything?

00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:13.000
That's a tricky one.

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:29.000
I can't answer that I'm afraid Paul.

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:32.000
Well that's fine and Helen you live with your parents?

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:33.000
Yeah.

00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:37.000
How did you find being around them?

00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:46.000
I didn't mind because I felt it brought us a bit closer because sometimes I don't see them all the time.

00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:52.000
That's wrong because I just stay with them once a week before lockdown.

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:56.000
But it seemed to have brought us closer because I've seen them all day now.

00:06:56.000 --> 00:07:00.000
When I even worked at home I wasn't living with them.

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:06.000
So if I was stuck on bits of work, they were always there.

00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:09.000
Mam can you let me with this or Dad?

00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:14.000
But I don't know what I would cope with if I was living on my own mind.

00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:18.000
It would probably be a bit different.

00:07:18.000 --> 00:07:25.000
I suppose if I was all living on my own I would have to move back in because I don't think I would cope living on my own like Richard.

00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:33.000
Did you ever both consider moving in with each other for the lockdown?

00:07:33.000 --> 00:07:35.000
No.

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:37.000
No.

00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:46.000
Because not long beginning to lockdown my father went back into hospital so I thought it wasn't a risk.

00:07:46.000 --> 00:07:54.000
You know that he wasn't as, I suppose it was serious but he didn't have a heart attack.

00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:57.000
It was his heart that was at.

00:07:57.000 --> 00:08:06.000
But if I wanted to go and see him it was really high risk of the Covid going back to him when he came out of hospital.

00:08:07.000 --> 00:08:12.000
So it was that way of dodgy.

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:18.000
Yeah and he was risky so we wouldn't take the risk.

00:08:18.000 --> 00:08:21.000
No that's fair enough.

00:08:21.000 --> 00:08:26.000
So on top of everything else, Helen you had your father being a bit under the weather.

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:28.000
Yeah.

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:31.000
So how did you find all of that?

00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:34.000
So you didn't visit him in hospital or anything?

00:08:34.000 --> 00:08:39.000
No I couldn't. My mother and my sister took him in.

00:08:39.000 --> 00:08:44.000
Luckily we got good doctors, really good doctors.

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:48.000
And he went to an appointment on a Monday, he was in on a Tuesday.

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:58.000
And they took him over, I wasn't with them, but they took him through the door and they weren't allowed to go through the hospital.

00:08:58.000 --> 00:09:02.000
They were only allowed to go into a certain type of ward I think.

00:09:02.000 --> 00:09:05.000
And left him there for about two weeks.

00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:12.000
And we were only watching what we were doing now on Skype or FaceTime etc.

00:09:12.000 --> 00:09:17.000
And that's what we did every day.

00:09:17.000 --> 00:09:22.000
But a totally odd and totally easy way of visiting.

00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:28.000
Did you find that? How did you find that emotionally having your father in for two weeks and not being able to see him?

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:30.000
Hard.

00:09:30.000 --> 00:09:35.000
Especially now, I say now I've grown up.

00:09:35.000 --> 00:09:39.000
I've never really left him in hospital.

00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:45.000
Since he was 71, so since he's 70 he's bad.

00:09:45.000 --> 00:09:47.000
It's a hard problem.

00:09:47.000 --> 00:09:53.000
And the only time I've left him for longer is when he had a two day pass.

00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:55.000
I didn't see him.

00:09:55.000 --> 00:10:02.000
I was told by my father, do not come and see me, it won't be well.

00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:11.000
But as long as seeing him not being with me in the house was already emotionally difficult.

00:10:11.000 --> 00:10:21.000
Because when he was in having his pacemaker removed and the right witred, when I left him I got in the lift and cried.

00:10:21.000 --> 00:10:22.000
Yes you did.

00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:27.000
Because I'd never have left him in hospital.

00:10:27.000 --> 00:10:33.000
And did Richard, you and Helen talk about that when it was happening?

00:10:33.000 --> 00:10:35.000
Yes, we did, we spoke a lot didn't we?

00:10:35.000 --> 00:10:37.000
Yes.

00:10:37.000 --> 00:10:42.000
And with friends as well.

00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:44.000
We liked friends.

00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:50.000
Sometimes they've had a difficult moment and they would support me.

00:10:50.000 --> 00:10:52.000
Yes.

00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:56.000
Which is good actually.

00:10:56.000 --> 00:11:02.000
So thinking about your friends, have you managed to stay in touch with them?

00:11:02.000 --> 00:11:05.000
Yes, very much.

00:11:05.000 --> 00:11:08.000
Mostly every day.

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:14.000
Either text or the semen for example, we are doing the Skype.

00:11:14.000 --> 00:11:16.000
Yes.

00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:21.000
And then we'd say two or three months in a bit and we'd start doing quizzes.

00:11:21.000 --> 00:11:24.000
Yes we did, we started doing quizzes now and it's been really enjoyable.

00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:27.000
It keeps your brain in gear.

00:11:27.000 --> 00:11:32.000
Which I do the quizzes really, I don't take part, I just do the quiz.

