No, there isn't actually.

00:17:49.000 --> 00:17:52.000
No.

00:17:52.000 --> 00:18:03.000
So thinking about the last seven months, how has it affected your wellbeing, your mood and how you feel about things?

00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:06.000
Sometimes when you've been on your own quite a bit.

00:18:06.000 --> 00:18:08.000
I've got my parents across the road if I need them.

00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:12.000
But sometimes when you just feel down in the dumps sometimes.

00:18:12.000 --> 00:18:15.000
Everything we take for granted these days, don't we?

00:18:15.000 --> 00:18:20.000
So things, you know, being able to go out whenever you feel like it, see anybody you wish to see.

00:18:20.000 --> 00:18:22.000
And I know it's all been taken away.

00:18:22.000 --> 00:18:26.000
It makes you appreciate life in a more way, you know.

00:18:26.000 --> 00:18:31.000
And it really is how much you take for granted these days.

00:18:31.000 --> 00:18:36.000
Because especially I feel a bit down in the dumps when we get to see friends on Skype.

00:18:36.000 --> 00:18:44.000
Because normally, say, on a Saturday, how it means, what we do on a Saturday is actually meeting up with our friend Albie.

00:18:44.000 --> 00:18:46.000
In his house.

00:18:46.000 --> 00:18:50.000
And I tend to go and get our friend Kerry.

00:18:50.000 --> 00:18:56.000
Because he lives, I think, supposedly down by you, Paul, in the sub-oath.

00:18:56.000 --> 00:19:00.000
So I go down and pick him up.

00:19:00.000 --> 00:19:05.000
Come up to as far as Richard, so Richard gets on the bus to go out, don't we?

00:19:05.000 --> 00:19:11.000
So I do miss that bit, just picking him up and having our own chat.

00:19:12.000 --> 00:19:14.000
With Kerry.

00:19:14.000 --> 00:19:17.000
I know it sounds bad to say, well, Richard being there.

00:19:17.000 --> 00:19:25.000
But he keeps saying to me, I'm like his sister, and he's like my brother, and we miss all that connection.

00:19:25.000 --> 00:19:33.000
Really, it makes me, I don't know, appreciate things now.

00:19:33.000 --> 00:19:37.000
If I didn't do it before, I'd just be on.

00:19:37.000 --> 00:19:39.000
Because I should have missed the things.

00:19:39.000 --> 00:19:42.000
We're supposed to take for granted, really.

00:19:42.000 --> 00:19:44.000
Yeah.

